  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I make clothes in Roblox?",
  "response": "Creating clothes in Roblox involves using image editing software to design the texture, and then uploading it to Roblox. Here's a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Get Templates:**\n   Roblox provides templates for shirts, pants, and t-shirts. These templates are essential as they show the layout and dimensions required. You can find these templates in the Roblox Developer Hub or by searching online for \"Roblox clothes templates.\"\n\n2. **Design Your Clothes:**\n   Use an image editing software like Photoshop, GIMP, or any other tool you are comfortable with to design your clothing. The templates will show the different parts of the clothes, such as the front, back, sleeves, and so on. Ensure you follow the dimensions accurately.\n\n   - **Shirts & Pants:** You will need to color and design within the provided frames in the templates. Pay attention to where the different sections of clothes will be wrapped around the avatar.\n   - **T-Shirts:** These are simpler as they require just a single image that gets displayed on the front of the avatar\u2019s torso.\n\n3. **Save Your Design:**\n   Once you have created your design, save it as a PNG file to maintain the transparency if necessary.\n\n4. **Upload to Roblox:**\n   - **Go to the Roblox website:**\n     - Log in to your Roblox account.\n     - Click on the \"Create\" button at the top of the screen.\n     - Choose \"Shirts,\" \"Pants,\" or \"T-Shirts\" depending on what you designed.\n   \n   - **Upload your image:**\n     - Click the \"Choose File\" button and select your saved PNG file.\n     - Once selected, you can name your clothing item.\n     - Click the \"Upload\" button.\n\n5. **Configure Your Clothing Item:**\n   - After uploading, go to \u201cDevelop\u201d page (accessible via the \u201cCreate\u201d button).\n   - Find your clothing item under \u201cShirts,\u201d \u201cPants,\u201d or \u201cT-Shirts.\u201d\n   - Click on the gear icon next to the item and select \u201cConfigure.\u201d\n   - Here, you can add a description, set the price if you wish to sell, and adjust other settings.\n\n6. **Testing your Clothes:**\n   - You can wear your clothing item on your avatar to test and see how it looks.\n   - Go to your avatar page and try your new item out.\n\nRemember, to upload shirts and pants, you need to have a Roblox Premium membership. However, uploading t-shirts does not require a premium account. Always ensure your designs comply with Roblox\u2019s community guidelines to avoid any issues.",
